cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method to improve feature attribution in neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper focuses on pruning the network for a given input to keep only neurons that highly contribute to the prediction, which is related to network architecture and optimization (cs.LG). The method is evaluated on image data, which suggests that it is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the theoretical justification of the pruning approach, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses benchmarks to evaluate the proposed method, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
